
Cartography
class
Cartography (from Greek χάρτης khartēs, \"map\"; and γράφειν graphein, \"write\") is the study and practice of making maps. Combining science, aesthetics, and technique, cartography builds on the premise that reality can be modeled in ways that communicate spatial information effectively. The fundamental problems of traditional cartography are to:[citation needed] Modern cartography constitutes many theoretical and practical foundations of geographic information systems.
